DIGEST
SB 32 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session McMath
Proposed law establishes a Perinatal Bereavement Care Initiative within the La. Dept. of
Health, office on women's health and community health.
Proposed law requires the office to coordinate with the Commission on Perinatal Care and
Prevention of Infant Mortality and nonprofit organizations to provide perinatal bereavement
resources to hospitals that provide maternity care or neonatal intensive care unit.
Proposed law requires the office to prioritize hospitals that lack access to a perinatal cooling
device, treat a high number of high-risk maternal patients, and deliver a high number of
babies.
Proposed law authorizes the La. Dept. of Health to seek and receive federal funds, gifts,
grants, and donations for purposes of implementing proposed law.
Proposed law requires the La. Dept. of Health to submit an annual progress report on the
progress of the initiative beginning Feb. 1, 2027, through Feb. 1, 2030, to the Senate and
House committees on health and welfare.
Proposed law provides that proposed law shall be known and may be cited as "Angel's Law".
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends the heading of Part XII-A of Ch. 5-B of Title 40 of the La. Revised Statutes of
1950; adds R.S. 40:1124.3)
